result.adr_address: 32-40號 Wellington St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Yung Kee Restaurant

reviews.text: If you have only one shot at trying out the roast goose in Hong Kong, this is the place to go. They have been in operations for more than half a century. The roast goose is here is tender and juicy. The other dishes are remarkable as well. I came back the next day to purchase some Chinese sausages for mom. Alas, it was a business dinner and I couldn't take out my phone to snap each dish!
Good roast goose meat and good service staff. The soup is superb! A little pricey place.

This is still a great restaurant after so many years. This is according to my Wife and friends who have been here on numerous occasions. I have been to Hong Kong over the last 20 years but never visited.

I told myself to booked in advance for my next trip to Hong Kong. I must say that I was not disappointed despite its size which was smaller than I have expected. This is because I have had goose in Taiwan and Malaysia that were huge in comparison.

The premium pork belly was good but would have been better if it did not taste so porky. Overall a great experience and I would recommend it.

It’s about 6 mins walk from central station.

A roast meat restaurant and a place to die for! Great ambience , service and food. Obviously the roast goose and char siu are really out of this world. Standards have been maintained over the years. Will continue to pursue the good life of dining experience here
Amazing food, service with a smile!! We were very happy with our meal. The waiter recommended the double boiled abalone soup which was super awesome!!
